      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That sounds like a pretty firm stance. But isn't it a bit of a false choice? If a government ignores social safety nets to pay down debt, doesn't that actually hurt the economy in the long run because people can't afford to participate? Why do you say debt has to be the actual priority over people's immediate needs?",
